The Covid-19 pandemic has changed the way private equity capital is allocated, with investors moving away from infrastructure and energy projects in favour of financing e-commerce start-ups, particularly companies that operate in the education and health-care industries. Business Day TV spoke to CEO of the Southern African Venture Capital & Private Equity Association CEO Tanya van Lill for more insight. Or listen to the full audio: Subscribe for free episodes: iono.fm | Apple Podcasts | Spotify | Pocket Casts | Player.fm